{#-
  products_edismax.j2 — canonical Apache Solr edismax template for the demo
  ``products`` collection. Renders to a Solr request-parameter dict.

  Declared params (all surfaced in the Optuna search-space the tutorial defines):
    title_boost                  float   range 0.5–10
    description_boost            float   range 0.5–10
    bullet_points_boost          float   range 0.5–10
    tie                          float   range 0.0–1.0
    mm                           string  e.g. "2<-25% 9<-3" or "75%"

  Output dict mixes Solr-native + unified-pivot keys:
    defType / q / pf / fl / rows  — Solr-native, passed through unchanged.
    field_boosts                  — pivoted to qf by SolrAdapter.render.
    tie_breaker                   — pivoted to tie.
    min_should_match              — pivoted to mm.

  Param names are flat (no dots) because the Jinja2 sandbox forbids
  attribute access (``field_boosts.title`` would fail at render time).

  The space stays under the 10^6 cardinality cap with 3 floats × 100
  buckets each. ``tie_breaker`` and ``mm`` are search-space dimensions.
-#}
{
  "defType": "edismax",
  "q": {{ query_text | tojson }},
  "field_boosts": {
    "title": {{ title_boost }},
    "description": {{ description_boost }},
    "bullet_points": {{ bullet_points_boost }}
  },
  "tie_breaker": {{ tie }},
  "min_should_match": "{{ mm }}",
  "fl": "*,score"
}
